structure.unit: B HOUSING, BUILDINGS, AND CONSTRUCTION - BUILDING CODE

law.catch_line: Reciprocity for licensees of other states.
law.text: Any person who has been issued a license in another state which has licensing, educational, and experience requirements substantially equal to or greater than those of this state and which grants equal licensing privileges to persons licensed in this state, may be issued an equivalent license in this state upon terms and conditions determined by the board.
law.history: Created 1994 Ky. Acts ch. 59, sec. 9, effective July 15, 1994.
